  URL =          "http://visinfo.zib.de/EVlib/Show?EVL-2004-154",
  abstract =     "Implicit models provide an accurate and flexible
                 representation of a surface. Although they have been
                 widely used in modeling contexts, their application to
                 visualization has been relatively limited due to
                 rendering difficulties. Typical explicit triangulation
                 of the surface, though effective, results in a
                 redundant representation and a high load on the bus
