                 ex-pressed by labeling rules are argued to be of key
                 importance for segmentation. Interframe motion of
                 object(s) and background is approximated by a
                 similarity or affine transforms. The computation
                 proceeds in several steps: (1) color gradient edges are
                 fuzzy-clustered according to their motion; (2)
                 boundaries of regions formed by a color segmenter are
